Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.41,0:00:02.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Flowing water has no form.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.98,0:00:04.71,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A blowing wind can't be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.71,0:00:06.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All cases can be freely deduced!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.68,0:00:08.75,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today is a special with cursed masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.75,0:00:10.95,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A mysterious room and an eerie smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.95,0:00:12.59,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.59,0:00:14.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.01,0:00:16.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.70,0:02:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, drive careful, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.11,0:02:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.24,0:02:04.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, you're going to be performing on a charity show held for children
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.24,0:02:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who have lost their families in car accidents next week, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.18,0:02:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you get into an accident in a place like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.12,0:02:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we couldn't face up to Beniko Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the hostess who chose you as a guest!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.23,0:02:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.06,0:02:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} invited us to a party today too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.73,0:02:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I get in an accident, I'll miss out on all the good food!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.73,0:02:27.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.21,0:02:29.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} used to be a famous singer, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.91,0:02:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.23,0:02:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She used to a big star. They called her the Canary of the Orient.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.94,0:02:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But nowadays she's so busy being the president
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:39.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of a show-biz promotion company called Kurenai Promotion
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.98,0:02:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that she's hardly ever on stage anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.94,0:02:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.99,0:02:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.46,0:02:56.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is this tree lying in the middle of the road like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.53,0:02:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, there's something posted on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.43,0:03:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.80,0:03:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't take part in the charity party held by Beniko Suo. You'll regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.21,0:03:12.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Messenger of the Cursed Masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.48,0:03:13.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.51,0:03:14.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.01,0:03:17.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Messenger of the Cursed Masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.14,0:03:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.50,0:03:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is some mansion, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.11,0:03:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.51,0:03:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masanori Katagiri, the photographer...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.52,0:03:55.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the one who travels around the world taking pictures of beautiful landscapes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.85,0:03:56.40,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Masanori Katagiri (45)\NPhotographer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.32,0:04:07.95,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mamoru Matsudaira (24)\NPro Baseball Player
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.66,0:04:05.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The King of Home Runs, baseball player Mamoru Matsudaira?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.40,0:04:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? And you're that famous detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.53,0:04:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.40,0:04:11.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.09,0:04:14.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you guests on next week's charity show too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.47,0:04:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.91,0:04:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a beauty!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.05,0:04:25.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's Haruka Nagara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.75,0:04:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the tarot card reader who's all the rage on TV and in the magazines?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.99,0:04:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know her too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.99,0:04:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whenever I step up to the plate, I read her predictions
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.93,0:04:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and put on gloves that match her lucky color of the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.33,0:04:40.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And that's how you became the King of Home Runs?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.67,0:04:43.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:45.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What seems to be the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.11,0:04:50.16,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Haruka Nagara (25)\NTarot Card Reader
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.00,0:04:49.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel something ominous about this mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.21,0:04:52.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel that there is going to be a great disaster...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.48,0:04:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What an eerie thing to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.01,0:04:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, rather than talk out here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.95,0:04:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,shouldn't we ask to be let in?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.75,0:05:00.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.55,0:05:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But which door do we use to get into the mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.23,0:05:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are two entrances...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.90,0:05:16.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you all for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.23,0:05:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so that side's the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.24,0:05:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you all for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.71,0:05:26.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.76,0:05:31.87,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Honami Shimogasa (21)\NSuo House Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.25,0:05:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} and his party, please enter from this sideâ€”the east entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.25,0:05:34.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.41,0:05:40.50,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Minaho Shimogasa (21)\NSuo House Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.79,0:05:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, Matsudaira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} and Nagara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.85,0:05:40.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,please enter from this sideâ€”the west entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.36,0:05:43.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are we going in separately?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.60,0:05:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inside of this mansion is divided into west and east.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.30,0:05:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those who will be spending the night in the rooms on the west side,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.93,0:05:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,enter from the west entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.17,0:05:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those who will be spending the night in the rooms on the east side,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.01,0:05:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,enter from the east entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.88,0:05:59.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is a tradition practiced here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.31,0:06:03.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What a strange place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.08,0:06:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we don't stick to traditional practices in this mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:08.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grave misfortune will befall us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.12,0:06:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misfortune?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.79,0:06:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.72,0:06:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because this is the place where...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.73,0:06:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because this is the place where...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.79,0:06:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- ...the cursed masks reside.\N- ...the cursed masks reside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.60,0:06:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cursed masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.66,0:06:45.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.92,0:06:47.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.33,0:06:51.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} likes to collect masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.73,0:06:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.28,0:07:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one's a cat mask...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.78,0:07:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your luggage has already been brought here,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.38,0:07:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so please wait in the mask room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.72,0:07:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mask room?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.16,0:07:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.57,0:07:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.94,0:07:34.28,Signs,,0,0,0,,E
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.94,0:07:34.28,Signs,,0,0,0,,2ND FLOOR
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.94,0:07:34.28,Signs,,0,0,0,,W
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.94,0:07:34.28,Signs,,0,0,0,,MASK ROOM
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.70,0:07:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This room connects the east and west wings of the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.74,0:07:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, this is fantastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.57,0:07:38.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are so many masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.42,0:07:55.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at all this...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.30,0:07:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.50,0:08:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A remote control?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.58,0:08:06.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.33,0:08:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.11,0:08:14.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}W-What's with all these masks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.78,0:08:16.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.05,0:08:18.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are all these masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.85,0:08:20.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are called the masks of Jofre{drop back and punt... there's no way you can get this from Joburuu, but at least this name exists in Spain, and it's what Catalan uses, so mnyeh}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.82,0:08:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You are...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.08,0:08:27.75,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Beniko Suo (63)\NSinger âˆ™ President of Kurenai Promotion
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.39,0:08:25.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beniko Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.06,0:08:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, everyone, for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.34,0:08:33.84,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kazuyo Inaba (40)\NSuo's Secretary
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.57,0:08:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you like my precious collection?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.24,0:08:41.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, yes, well, I guess you could say...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.51,0:08:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just mentioned the masks of Jofre,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.88,0:08:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but are you referring to the masks covering the side wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.78,0:08:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is said that the Spanish sculptor,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.38,0:08:52.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jofre Gonzales, made them just before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.62,0:08:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are the two hundred masks that he made.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.05,0:08:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are also called the Cursed Masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.39,0:09:00.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cursed Masks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.19,0:09:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, what are these cursed masks all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.60,0:09:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jofre Gonzales is a sculptor of tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.13,0:09:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although overflowing with talent,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,trapped by the jealousy of his brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.70,0:09:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,his fame, glory and estate were all taken away from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:19.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jofre, who became very wary of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.51,0:09:23.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,began making masks as if obsessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.35,0:09:28.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After finishing his two-hundredth mask, he killed himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.22,0:09:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks were scattered upon his body and splattered with blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as if they had sucked the blood from him while he was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.09,0:09:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since then, Jofre's reputation was restored,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.03,0:09:42.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and his masks were handed down to various people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.37,0:09:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But many who owned the masks seem to have died tragically.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.24,0:09:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An English bank president fell off his horse
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.78,0:09:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the following day after getting hold of one of the masks, and died.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.31,0:09:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A French jeweler was attacked by robbers and killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.72,0:10:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with the passing of time, these masks became known
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.29,0:10:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as the cursed masks that sip the blood of their owners,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.16,0:10:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and were feared by people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.86,0:10:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, owning all two hundred of those masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.00,0:10:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.43,0:10:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had a master spiritualist seal the curse in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.20,0:10:22.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's starting to get more and more occult around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.61,0:10:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.61,0:10:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the evil will of a living person may be even more frightening than a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.41,0:10:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.55,0:10:35.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, on our way here, our path was blocked by a fallen tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.48,0:10:37.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and we found this pinned to the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.62,0:10:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! I received a similar letter three days ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got one too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.23,0:10:47.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.37,0:10:48.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.10,0:10:51.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It seems to be more than just a prank...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.34,0:10:54.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the office also sent me a strange letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.97,0:10:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toya, you're late!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.15,0:11:01.95,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Toya Aikawa (26)\NRock Singer
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.58,0:11:00.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm right in the midst of a nationwide tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.01,0:11:02.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.31,0:11:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.58,0:11:06.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, don't you know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.25,0:11:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the popular #1 rock singer Toya Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.46,0:11:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You received a strange letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.26,0:11:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The name of the sender is not written.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.26,0:11:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way the name of the addressee is written is also odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.80,0:11:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems a ruler was used so that the handwriting cannot be identified.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.27,0:11:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.04,0:11:27.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.34,0:11:32.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.71,0:11:37.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cursed masks will sip blood tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.21,0:11:39.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Messenger of the Cursed Masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.59,0:11:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you should call the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.99,0:11:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.72,0:11:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since I've started the charity show, I've been bothered by pranks like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.67,0:11:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, this stew is very delicious indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.55,0:12:04.18,Character Card,,0,0,0,,East Wing, First Floor\NDining Room
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.14,0:12:02.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This wine sure is good too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.14,0:12:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Top class!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.94,0:12:07.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, I am greatly thankful
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.88,0:12:10.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you have all graciously accepted to appear as guests
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.82,0:12:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on the charity show that I will be hosting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.95,0:12:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, may I ask you a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.29,0:12:19.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.82,0:12:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you come across the idea of saving children
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.16,0:12:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,whose parents who have become victims of traffic accidents?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.43,0:12:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I started this charity about 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:36.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to tell the truth, my manager caused a hit-and-run accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.57,0:12:37.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hit-and-run?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.71,0:12:39.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Ever since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.61,0:12:43.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could not stand being indifferent to traffic accidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.45,0:12:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are people saying that she's a publicity seeker,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.59,0:12:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it's really nothing like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.56,0:12:54.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um... What happened to the manager after the incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.63,0:12:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.03,0:12:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That manager happened to be my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.43,0:13:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.10,0:13:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I lost my father at a young age,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.04,0:13:06.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after my mother died, I was sent around to my relatives' homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.90,0:13:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really had it tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.37,0:13:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} here helped me in every way she could.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.51,0:13:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm what I am today thanks to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.45,0:13:21.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toya's mother was more a cherished friend of mine than a manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.09,0:13:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are many at Kurenai Promotion
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.99,0:13:26.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who have lost their families in traffic accidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.36,0:13:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0} is putting a lot of effort in helping the children
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.76,0:13:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of traffic accident victims become independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.43,0:13:35.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a touching story!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.63,0:13:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll cooperate as much as I can at your charity show next week!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.90,0:13:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.51,0:13:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I lost my wife in a car accident 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.74,0:13:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that my wife in heaven is happy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.65,0:13:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that I'm going to be taking part in Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s charity show too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.41,0:13:57.79,Character Card,,0,0,0,,West Wing, Third Floor\NSuo's Living Room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.95,0:13:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I'd like you to investigate something for me, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.29,0:13:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.76,0:14:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd like me to figure out the one who sent out those letters, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.96,0:14:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.30,0:14:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I wonder if you can check in detail
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.27,0:14:11.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on the traffic accident that took Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:13.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.17,0:14:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I ask you why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.97,0:14:17.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is something that bothers me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.44,0:14:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would 2 million yen be enough to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.31,0:14:22.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,2 million yen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.85,0:14:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd be more than glad to!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.89,0:14:33.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're pretty good, King of Home Runs!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:34.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.14,0:14:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you play very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.36,0:14:43.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, this year is a good year for you to begin something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.97,0:14:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something new?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.97,0:14:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why then, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, how about making a debut as a singer from our company?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.16,0:14:55.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it'll make a great hit if it is sung by\Nthe modern-day great detective, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.28,0:14:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I'll sing you a song then!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.78,0:14:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- We're sorry...\N- We're sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.65,0:15:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, when the clock strikes midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.72,0:15:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we have a tradition of locking the door of the mask room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.96,0:15:08.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the door is locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.56,0:15:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we will not be able to pass back and forth between the east and west wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.92,0:15:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we would like you to go into your rooms before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.64,0:15:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.04,0:15:21.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Midnight is still too early to close up...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.24,0:15:25.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a reason for locking the doors at midnight?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.10,0:15:28.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks of Jofre like pranks
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.05,0:15:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and begin playing on their own come midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.55,0:15:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we must lock the door and keep them confined.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.94,0:15:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.55,0:15:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.86,0:15:40.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come morning, the masks are tilted unnaturally...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.86,0:15:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...or down on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.73,0:15:44.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has happened many times now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.30,0:15:49.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Now, please go into your rooms, everyone.\N- Now, please go into your rooms, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.20,0:15:54.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Can this story get any more occult?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.38,0:16:52.34,Character Card,,0,0,0,,East Wing, Second Floor\NGuest Room
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.16,0:16:56.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ugh, his snoring is so loud{lit. annoying}, I can't sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.74,0:17:00.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An extension phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.01,0:17:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.34,0:17:08.79,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Messenger of the Cursed Masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.79,0:17:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Messenger of the Cursed Masks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.35,0:17:13.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gimme that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.42,0:17:14.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.09,0:17:17.15,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The cursed masks thirst for blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.15,0:17:19.82,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who will be the sacrifice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.82,0:17:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.02,0:17:22.79,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You'd better hurry before it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.49,0:17:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.23,0:17:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.50,0:17:35.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, Conan, wake Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} up and bring the key to this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.07,0:17:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.93,0:17:58.16,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's locked...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.06,0:18:01.13,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The call a while ago was from an extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.13,0:18:03.35,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The person is in the mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.07,0:18:06.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.54,0:18:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the key!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.01,0:18:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.66,0:18:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.88,0:18:22.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks of Jofre are gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.22,0:18:25.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.16,0:18:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that just now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.09,0:18:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It came from above!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.70,0:18:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Above? That's Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bedroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.23,0:18:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't go that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.17,0:18:43.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to get to her room, you have to take the stairs on the west side!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.08,0:18:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This door is locked too...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.21,0:18:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll wake Minaho and make her open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.35,0:18:54.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what on earth is this racket about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.22,0:18:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the night...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.45,0:18:57.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks of Jofre are...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.96,0:19:07.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.31,0:19:18.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.44,0:19:21.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This door is locked too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.18,0:19:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Break that glass!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.98,0:19:27.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.18,0:19:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something happen to Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.27,0:19:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, how's {\i1}Sensei{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.47,0:19:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like she's hurt. She's bleeding badly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.74,0:19:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks of Jofre are scattered all over the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.67,0:19:52.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks of Jofre?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.94,0:19:55.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any other way in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.68,0:19:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's another door over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.04,0:20:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That door's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.05,0:20:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been sealed off for quite a while already!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.12,0:20:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go in through there and check out the inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.26,0:20:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess there is no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.79,0:20:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! Here you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.67,0:20:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.31,0:20:24.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The door is looked, all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.58,0:20:26.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Two locks!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.98,0:20:28.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and go check on Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.59,0:20:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No good... We're too late...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.59,0:20:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Son of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.09,0:20:45.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.54,0:20:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.32,0:21:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't come in! Please stay here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.68,0:21:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her throat slashed with one stroke...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.95,0:21:09.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How cruel...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.55,0:21:11.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.22,0:21:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was this a murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.42,0:21:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.76,0:21:15.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door was locked, wasn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.83,0:21:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the looks of the corpse, suicide is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.59,0:21:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.36,0:21:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My curse has been fulfilled...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.57,0:21:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.10,0:21:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a declaration that a murder will be committed,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.07,0:21:31.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from the Messenger of the Cursed Masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.71,0:21:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.85,0:21:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curse of the masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.65,0:21:42.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was cursed to death by the masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.79,0:21:45.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Suo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was cursed to death by the masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.99,0:21:47.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.66,0:21:49.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the crime scene is a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.46,0:21:54.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How did the murderer manage to kill Suo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.10,0:22:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Messenger of the Cursed Masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.10,0:22:09.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you report it to the police when you first found this letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.91,0:22:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the victim, Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} mentioned that she had been receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.48,0:22:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,similar pranks for some time, and not to worry about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.45,0:22:19.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, these are the cursed masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.25,0:22:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.12,0:22:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard a groan and a loud crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.99,0:22:28.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could've been the sound of the killer scattering the masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.66,0:22:32.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said that this door was locked from inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.60,0:22:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's why I broke the glass above the door, made Conan go inside
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.53,0:22:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and verified Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.07,0:22:42.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door was definitely locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.74,0:22:43.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both locks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.14,0:22:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two locks?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.11,0:22:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.14,0:22:49.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} always locked both locks on her door.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.35,0:22:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.72,0:22:52.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,this lock...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.48,0:22:55.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then this padlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.47,0:22:58.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did the victim have two locks on her door?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.32,0:23:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, according to her secretary, Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.46,0:23:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to have the curse of the masks sealed in by a spiritualist,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.20,0:23:09.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she was told to do several things.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.73,0:23:15.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them was to put two locks on the bedroom door.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.34,0:23:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A spiritualist, eh...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.47,0:23:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the victim herself opened the door and let the victim in?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.35,0:23:26.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it doesn't seem like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.89,0:23:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was suffering from insomnia lately,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.89,0:23:33.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and was taking sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.69,0:23:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why there were no traces of the victim struggling?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.53,0:23:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the victim locked the door as usual, took sleeping pills and went to bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.90,0:23:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,how did the killer get into the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.44,0:23:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this door?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.00,0:23:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a bedroom next door too,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.57,0:23:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but that door seems to have been closed off for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.65,0:23:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems to be nailed shut,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.55,0:23:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and there are no signs of it having been opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.32,0:24:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The railing above the door, can that bar be removed?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.05,0:24:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked on it, but it couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.39,0:24:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The space between the bars is about 5 or 6 centimeters,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.36,0:24:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so not even an arm can go through.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.93,0:24:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about that window on the other side?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.66,0:24:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That window is fixed on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.80,0:24:16.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is nothing out of the ordinary about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.20,0:24:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, how and where did the killer go in and out of this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.27,0:24:26.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only door that could be opened and shut was locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.74,0:24:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door to the bedroom next door is nailed and sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.95,0:24:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The space between the bars above it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.32,0:24:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is so narrow that not even an arm can get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.72,0:24:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The windows are both fixed on,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.52,0:24:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and there seems to be nothing wrong with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.82,0:24:40.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's also impossible for the victim herself to have opened the door
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.52,0:24:43.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and let the killer in, because she was under the effect of sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.66,0:24:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The room is a locked room, with no way in or out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.40,0:24:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really took the sleeping pills herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.10,0:24:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she didn't take them herself, who would make her...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.74,0:24:56.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Wait a sec...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.74,0:24:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.81,0:25:00.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.01,0:25:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer met Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.38,0:25:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,made her drink something with a sleeping pill in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.72,0:25:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and put her to sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.95,0:25:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the killer carried Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to her bed and killed her there!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.62,0:25:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.76,0:25:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, how did the killer lock the door when leaving the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.49,0:25:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.76,0:25:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't figured that out yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.06,0:25:21.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.23,0:25:25.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Only half of the locked room mystery can be explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.17,0:25:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door is the only possible way that the killer could've entered,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.77,0:25:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but how did the killer lock the door from the outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.78,0:25:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the lock were just a handle that could be turned,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.78,0:25:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then using a string or something could unlock it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.67,0:25:40.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the problem is the padlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.88,0:25:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to lock this, the door has to be closed first.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.92,0:25:47.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the door and the metal piece on the door frame have to be matched.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.32,0:25:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only after doing that can the pole be stuck into the two metal fixtures.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.40,0:25:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's possible to do all this from outside the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.67,0:26:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of trick did the killer use?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.54,0:26:02.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No matter what trick the killer used,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.57,0:26:04.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}why didn't the killer make it look like a suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.67,0:26:08.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}after doing all this to kill her?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.28,0:26:12.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The killer called our room just before the murder was committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.22,0:26:15.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As if to let us know beforehand that murder was going to take place...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.89,0:26:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This knife seems to be the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.22,0:26:22.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what was decorated in the room of the masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.26,0:26:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was poked into the bed pole, but there's something odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.70,0:26:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you can see, its handle is also smeared with blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.13,0:26:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure is odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.14,0:26:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the killer is holding the handle, there should be no blood there...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.14,0:26:38.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.41,0:26:41.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there were masks among the masks that were scattered on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.91,0:26:44.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with blood splattered on them too.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.08,0:26:48.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was found on the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.69,0:26:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems to have been splattered with blood at close range.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.02,0:26:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that the killer was wearing this mask when committing the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.36,0:27:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, there may be some traces of the killer left...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.50,0:27:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are there other masks that have been splattered with blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.30,0:27:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but it's quite strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.17,0:27:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the other masks had blood only around the mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.18,0:27:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, there's a frightening story about the masks of Jofre,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.81,0:27:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,saying they suck the very life out of their owners.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.78,0:27:21.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.32,0:27:25.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could the killer have scattered the masks
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.02,0:27:28.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to confuse investigations with occult stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.13,0:27:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.43,0:27:35.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I wonder if that's the only reason why the killer scattered the masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.53,0:27:38.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, I'm sure there's some other reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.60,0:27:40.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If I could only figure that out...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.07,0:27:41.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.18,0:27:43.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, how was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.21,0:27:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We checked everywhere around the mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.71,0:27:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but perhaps because of the snow that has accumulated,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.11,0:27:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there is no sign of the killer having gone in or out!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.22,0:27:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the killer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.35,0:27:56.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone inside the mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.75,0:27:59.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aside from Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and his family, those who were in this mansion are
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.16,0:28:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,photographer Masanori Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.69,0:28:06.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,pro baseball player Mamoru Matsudaira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.23,0:28:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,popular fortune-teller Haruka Nagara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.57,0:28:13.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,rock singer Toya Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.24,0:28:16.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the victim's secretary, Kazuyo Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.09,0:28:20.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the twin maids, Minaho and Honami Shimogasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.58,0:28:22.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That makes seven people.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.48,0:28:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can narrow down the suspects a bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.68,0:28:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.85,0:28:41.22,Signs,,0,0,0,,2ND FLOOR
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.85,0:28:41.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,W
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.87,0:28:41.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,E
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.87,0:28:41.24,Signs,,0,0,0,,MASK ROOM
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.42,0:28:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't get to Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bedroom on the third floor
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.72,0:28:34.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,without using the stairs in the west wing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.09,0:28:35.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of the incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.59,0:28:39.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the doors leading to the east and west wings were both locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.26,0:28:41.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has already been verified.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.30,0:28:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.37,0:28:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you couldn't pass from the east wing to the west wing at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.00,0:28:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the killer is someone
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.70,0:28:49.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who was in the west wing of the mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.14,0:28:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who were in what rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.00,0:28:58.02,Signs,,0,0,0,,E
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.00,0:28:57.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,1ST FLOOR
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.00,0:28:57.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,W
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.44,0:29:04.59,Signs,,0,0,0,,2ND FLOOR
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.34,0:28:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, on the first floor of the east wing were Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.68,0:28:58.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the west wing were Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Minaho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.42,0:29:00.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the second floor of the east wing were the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.78,0:29:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the west wing were Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Matsudaira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Haruka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.59,0:29:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see... There are five suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.03,0:29:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Matsudaira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Nagara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.80,0:29:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Minaho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.23,0:29:17.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yes, the messenger of the cursed masks
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.70,0:29:19.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}is one of those five!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.86,0:29:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.10,0:29:29.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hate to have to do this, knowing how tired you all must be,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.33,0:29:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I'd like to ask you a few questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.60,0:29:36.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The incident occurred in the early morning, at around 2:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.16,0:29:40.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell me, in order, what you were doing at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.01,0:29:42.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.45,0:29:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was fast asleep in my room until Ran came to wake me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.19,0:29:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got the key and headed for the second floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.62,0:29:53.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where do you keep the key?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.89,0:29:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the kitchen wall next to this dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.86,0:30:00.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So anybody could take it and use it at will?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.03,0:30:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the key was definitely there at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.70,0:30:04.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.68,0:30:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.44,0:30:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.84,0:30:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are there any spare keys?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.37,0:30:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are old keys, so we can't make spares.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.08,0:30:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we unlocked the door and went into the mask room,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.08,0:30:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we noticed that the masks of Jofre were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.68,0:30:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was when we heard the groan and loud noise from the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.56,0:30:28.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, and while we were waking Minaho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on the extension phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.26,0:30:30.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.34,0:30:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was sleeping in my room on the first floor too.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.93,0:30:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I realized that they had come to wake Honami,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.54,0:30:40.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I didn't think it was a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.14,0:30:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it started getting noisy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.78,0:30:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I went to the second floor to check things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.81,0:30:48.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was awakened by Honami on the extension phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.65,0:30:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,took the key and went to the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.65,0:30:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was also sleeping in my room,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.12,0:30:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but as it started to get noisy outside, I got up
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.99,0:31:00.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and went out into the corridor just as Minaho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had come up the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.53,0:31:02.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.63,0:31:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.86,0:31:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I heard that you did not appear at the time the corpse was found?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.80,0:31:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had too much wine to drink last night and was totally passed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.21,0:31:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you didn't notice all the racket going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.94,0:31:19.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.11,0:31:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, have you ever met Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} before?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.75,0:31:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I met her for the first time yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.89,0:31:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.75,0:31:35.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} asked me to check on the accident that took your wife's life 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.99,0:31:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.33,0:31:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea why?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.50,0:31:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.70,0:31:47.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Suo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} asked the old man to check on the accident that took Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s wife's life?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.74,0:31:51.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why would she want to check on a traffic accident that happened 20 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.18,0:31:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother got into a car accident twenty years ago too, didn't she, Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.32,0:32:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.32,0:32:02.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.23,0:32:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.62,0:32:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you tell us about the accident that took your wife's life?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.56,0:32:12.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll find out sooner or later even if I didn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.80,0:32:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, my wife was the victim of the car accident that Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mother had caused.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.29,0:32:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.37,0:32:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you know about it, Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.44,0:32:26.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No... because I was still only six years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.31,0:32:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how is that traffic accident connected to today's murder case?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.45,0:32:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police think that the murderer is among us, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.32,0:32:39.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way! Is that true, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.47,0:32:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.69,0:32:46.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recall that it had stopped snowing after 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.73,0:32:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll bet you couldn't find traces of the killer on the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.27,0:32:55.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is she right, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.44,0:32:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.34,0:33:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's true that there are no signs of the killer having entered or left the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.32,0:33:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.98,0:33:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the killer is among us?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.92,0:33:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, since the mask room was locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.89,0:33:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer has to be one of the five who were in the west wing!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.49,0:33:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Haruka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Matsudaira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or Minaho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.37,0:33:26.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh? Wait a sec... That was a strange remark.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.97,0:33:29.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why did he say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.71,0:33:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's difficult to single out the suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.91,0:33:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think there is a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.95,0:33:40.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that you're going to find the killer using your cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.79,0:33:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the looks of the scene of the crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.49,0:33:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer probably was splattered by a lot of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.12,0:33:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it is possible to avoid blood on the face by wearing the mask,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.66,0:33:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it would not be as easy to remove the blood from the hair and body.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.34,0:33:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! The killer is someone who had time to wipe the splattered blood off!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.67,0:34:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What? Are you saying that I'm the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.21,0:34:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only person who had time to wipe blood off
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.84,0:34:07.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is you, because you weren't at the scene where the body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.81,0:34:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.65,0:34:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would I have to kill Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.48,0:34:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.12,0:34:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut out your nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.89,0:34:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.06,0:34:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fraud fortune-teller!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.94,0:34:39.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it! That's what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.58,0:34:45.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I was completely deceived by the trap that the killer had set!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.28,0:34:49.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But now, this farce is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.05,0:34:52.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've figured out the curse of the masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.00,0:34:59.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's up, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.77,0:35:03.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Mouri says he has a favor to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.27,0:35:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.91,0:35:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the chest over there. Take a look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.48,0:35:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh well...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.72,0:35:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.46,0:35:31.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Leave the rest to me, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.41,0:35:42.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is the bedroom next door...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.34,0:35:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bedroom that looks just like Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s was right next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.15,0:35:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Correct. This room, with the same layout as the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.65,0:35:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is what helped solve the mystery of the locked doors
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.39,0:35:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as well as reveal the identity of the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.51,0:36:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is not the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.79,0:36:03.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been saying that I'm not!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.93,0:36:05.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you solved the mystery of the locked doors?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.73,0:36:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I've figured everything out.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.73,0:36:10.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So who is the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.17,0:36:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer who killed Beniko Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in a locked room,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.71,0:36:16.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the Messenger of the Cursed Masks is...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.01,0:36:21.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...you!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.31,0:36:28.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Messenger of the Cursed Masks is...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.72,0:36:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...you!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.25,0:36:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toya Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.92,0:36:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.99,0:36:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.16,0:36:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What on earth are you talking about, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.39,0:36:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I, who was in the east wing of the mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.50,0:36:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,have gone to {\i1}Sensei{\i0}'s bedroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.93,0:36:49.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's true that you could not go to Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.87,0:36:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to prove that,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.89,0:36:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you called us on the extension phone just before you committed the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.61,0:37:01.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if he couldn't go to her bedroom, how could he have committed the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.12,0:37:05.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been suspicious from the time the body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.22,0:37:09.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I kept wondering why the killer, despite committing the crime behind a locked door,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.59,0:37:12.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,didn't make her death look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.66,0:37:16.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because he couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.93,0:37:23.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} without entering her bedroom at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.27,0:37:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.17,0:37:27.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without going into her bedroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.04,0:37:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.61,0:37:34.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible, with the help of the cursed masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.18,0:37:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me that you really believe in things such as curses?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.69,0:37:47.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. But the masks of Jofre are indeed the key to committing this locked-room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.10,0:37:50.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will replay that method here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.23,0:37:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.14,0:37:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.94,0:38:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I borrowed a knife that is similar to the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.28,0:38:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a rubber rope attached through the hole at the rear end of the handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.61,0:38:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, the mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.93,0:38:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rubber rope is passed through both eyes of all the masks,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.39,0:38:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the rubber rope attached to the knife is passed through the mouth hole of all the masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.76,0:38:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all of us went to bed, Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.56,0:38:23.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,went to the kitchen to get the key to enter the mask room.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.69,0:38:26.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stole the masks of Jofre and a knife,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.23,0:38:29.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then locked the door and returned the key to the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.37,0:38:33.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He brought the masks and knife into this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.27,0:38:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and carried on with the rubber rope trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.98,0:38:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He dropped the masks and the knife
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.51,0:38:40.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,into Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bedroom through the space between the railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.31,0:38:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The size of the space is 5Ã—5 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.95,0:38:44.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A thin mask would easily slide through.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.85,0:38:49.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you really solve the mystery of the locked door doing something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.04,0:38:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, please watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.61,0:39:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the last mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.75,0:39:14.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After placing all the masks inside the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.92,0:39:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he pulled the rubber rope towards himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.90,0:39:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, everyone, since one mask is 15 millimeters thick,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.17,0:39:43.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if 200 are piled up one on top of another,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.41,0:39:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the pile would be 3 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.31,0:39:47.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The position of the neck of the victim asleep in bed
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.88,0:39:50.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was about 3.5 meters from the railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.55,0:39:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.80,0:40:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.58,0:40:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the edge of the knife to the victim's throat is only 10 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.25,0:40:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All he had left to do now was to push the masks out using a ruler or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.12,0:40:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By using the stairs that only the people in the east wing of the mansion can climb,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.10,0:40:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} without setting foot into her room at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.20,0:40:44.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! One of the masks was badly covered blood
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.97,0:40:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because it was the mask on the very top, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.87,0:40:50.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why several masks had blood by the mouth,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.98,0:40:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was because Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s splattered on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.58,0:40:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally, he severs the rubber rope that was passed through the eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.62,0:40:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of the masks and the handle of the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.32,0:41:05.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.30,0:41:11.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's your locked-room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.77,0:41:15.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all rubbish! Just where do you have the proof that I used that trick?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.24,0:41:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you're acting in bad faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.37,0:41:25.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you realized that you've already confessed that you are the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.98,0:41:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.28,0:41:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were being questioned a while ago, you said,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.09,0:41:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I noticed that the kids came to wake Honami up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.29,0:41:41.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, because I was in my room on the first floor then!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.43,0:41:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you said, those kids, who besides Ran were you referring to?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.80,0:41:46.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who else but the kid named Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.83,0:41:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh, how strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.40,0:41:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't say a word back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.51,0:41:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know I was with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.61,0:41:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.94,0:42:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, I opened the door a bit and looked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.28,0:42:03.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I know that you were with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.38,0:42:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.65,0:42:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.35,0:42:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it's even stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.72,0:42:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I didn't go with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.89,0:42:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to check if the doors around the house were locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.33,0:42:17.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.43,0:42:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.87,0:42:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.93,0:42:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.31,0:42:31.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did tell Ran and Conan to go get Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.34,0:42:36.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought the two of them went to Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room together,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.28,0:42:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because when you heard me say that, you were on the third floor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.49,0:42:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just because of something like that, you figured...!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.76,0:42:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toya! After all {\i1}Sensei{\i0} did for you, how could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.19,0:42:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up! After all she did for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.13,0:42:51.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.67,0:42:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That lady blamed the hit-and-run accident that she caused on my mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.40,0:42:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and made it look as if she committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.80,0:42:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.61,0:43:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true! But I only found out about it two months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.31,0:43:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was cleaning out my mother's belongings,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.48,0:43:09.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when a letter fell out from behind the cover of her diary
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.18,0:43:11.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the truth about the incident was written in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.90,0:43:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie! It's all rubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.22,0:43:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's not! Mother had an alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.99,0:43:22.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The accident occurred on the night of October 31!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.63,0:43:26.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,October 31...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.13,0:43:27.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s birthday...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.30,0:43:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! Mother was with me all day!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.41,0:43:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the one who hit my wife and ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.58,0:43:37.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...was Suo?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.18,0:43:40.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, she didn't even know that your wife
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.75,0:43:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was the victim of a traffic accident, Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.68,0:43:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess she asked me to investigate on the case
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.49,0:43:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after she heard Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} talk about it at dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.23,0:43:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0} is a fine person who has been hosting charity shows for 15 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.93,0:43:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.40,0:44:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That lady embezzled the money that was raised to fatten her own pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.60,0:44:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie! {\i1}Sensei{\i0} would never do any such thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.20,0:44:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You also got part of the cash, didn't you!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.14,0:44:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't talk as if you know nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.98,0:44:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to keep Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from participating in this corrupt charity
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.31,0:44:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,no matter what...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.65,0:44:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.15,0:44:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beniko Suo was a devil wearing the mask of someone practicing good will!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.72,0:44:26.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think that I felt grateful for her having saved me, all these years...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.16,0:44:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I... I...!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.42,0:46:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be that Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was possessed by the curse of the masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.16,0:46:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Curses are only superstitions!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.58,0:46:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A curse! This is a curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.68,0:46:30.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's no curse, old man. You're just a klutz.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.74,0:46:45.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That sounded like...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.05,0:46:46.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A gunshot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.95,0:46:55.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.06,0:47:01.99,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.99,0:47:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Rain shower
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.99,0:47:08.56,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The next episode airs April 10!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.56,0:47:10.79,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next week is the movie, The Last Wizard of the Century!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.79,0:47:11.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
